messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Files containing the implementation of App\Http\Controllers\PostLikeController::destroy

- app/Http/Controllers/PostLikeController.php

Explanation
- The route in routes/auth.php refers to App\Http\Controllers\PostLikeController (no sub-namespace). The destroy method for that class is implemented in app/Http/Controllers/PostLikeController.php. In that method the controller calls $post->dislike() and returns a MultiplePendingTurboStreamResponse updating the like button and likes count.
- There is another PostLikeController at app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/PostLikeController.php, but it is namespaced App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1 and therefore is not the controller referenced by the route in routes/auth.php.
